<title>SOUTH AFRICA: S.African March M3 money supply grows 16.39 pct.</title>
<headline>S.African March M3 money supply grows 16.39 pct.</headline>
<dateline>PRETORIA 1997-04-25</dateline>
<text>
<p>South Africa's year-on-year broadly defined M3 money supply grew 16.39 percent in March, preliminary Reserve Bank figures show.</p>
<p>February M3 growth was revised to 15.87 percent from a preliminary 15.82 percent.</p>
<p>Annual private sector credit growth was 15.96 percent, preliminary figures showed, against a revised 17.33 percent in February.</p>
<p>A Reuters consensus poll of economist forecast M3 year-on-year growth of 15.04 percent while private credit was seen expanding 16.50 percent.  </p>
<p>Detailed data (Percentage changes over 12 months):</p>
<p>March 1997 preliminary M3 growth -- 16.39 percent</p>
<p>March 1997 preliminary private sector credit growth -- 15.96 percent</p>
